# Ionide-Nvim

**F# support for Neovim**

_An unofficial part of the [Ionide](http://ionide.io) plugin suite._

## About Ionide-Nvim

* A (now disconnected) fork of [Ionide-Vim](https://github.com/ionide/ionide-vim), which is a fork of [fsharp/vim-fsharp](https://github.com/fsharp/vim-fsharp).

* Uses [FsAutoComplete](https://github.com/fsharp/FsAutoComplete) as a backend.

* Uses Neovim's built-in LSP client (requires Neovim 0.11+)

## Requirements

* **Neovim 0.11+** — uses native LSP features (`vim.lsp.config`, `vim.lsp.enable`, `vim.lsp.inlay_hint`, `vim.lsp.codelens`)

* [.NET SDK](https://dotnet.microsoft.com/download) — required to install and run FsAutoComplete

## Features

- Filetype detection for `.fs`, `.fsx`, `.fsi`, and `.fsproj` files
- Root detection cascade: `.slnx` → `.sln` → `.fsproj` → `.fsx` → `.git`
- Curated FSAC settings defaults (60+ settings with documentation)
- SDK version handling (`DOTNET_ROLL_FORWARD` for prerelease SDKs)
- Auto completions, diagnostics, quick fixes
- Go to Definition, Find References, Rename, Symbol Search
- Code lenses (signatures and references)
- Inlay hints
- Document highlights
- Optional signature help on cursor move
- Tooltips and signature help
- F# Interactive integration (send line/selection/buffer, toggle, quit, reset)
- fsproj file operations (move files up/down, add, remove, rename)
- FSAC-backed test discovery and test runs
- FSAC custom workspace/test/document notifications
- Integration with [FSharpLint](https://github.com/fsprojects/FSharpLint) and [Fantomas](https://github.com/fsprojects/fantomas/)

## Companion Plugin: sagefs.nvim

Ionide-Nvim provides **LSP integration and basic FSI** — completions, diagnostics, go-to-definition, references, code actions, and terminal-based FSI.

For **live development** — cell-based evaluation with `;;` boundaries, inline results, live testing with gutter markers, code coverage, hot reload, and AI agent integration via MCP — install [sagefs.nvim](https://github.com/WillEhrendreich/sagefs.nvim) alongside Ionide-Nvim.

| Concern | Ionide-Nvim | sagefs.nvim |
|---|---|---|
| LSP (completions, diagnostics, go-to-def, rename) | ✓ | — |
| Root detection, filetype handling, FSAC settings | ✓ | — |
| fsproj operations (move file up/down, add, remove, rename) | ✓ | — |
| Basic FSI (send line/selection/buffer to terminal) | ✓ (fallback) | — |
| Cell evaluation with `;;` boundaries + inline results | — | ✓ |
| Live unit testing with gutter markers | — | ✓ |
| Code coverage with gutter signs | — | ✓ |
| Hot reload (~100ms) | — | ✓ |
| MCP server for AI agents | — | ✓ |

**They don't conflict.** Ionide-Nvim's FSI opens a terminal buffer; sagefs.nvim communicates with SageFs over its own protocol. Both can be installed simultaneously.

## Getting Started

### Install FsAutoComplete

If you're not relying on Mason, install FsAutoComplete with `dotnet tool install`.

Global install: `dotnet tool install -g fsautocomplete`

Project-local install: `dotnet tool install fsautocomplete` at the project root, then configure `ionide.cmd`

### Setup

#### Neovim 0.11+ (native LSP, no lspconfig needed)

~~~lua
-- In your init.lua or a plugin spec:
local ionide_config = require("ionide").setup({})
vim.lsp.config("fsautocomplete", ionide_config)
vim.lsp.enable("fsautocomplete")
~~~

#### With nvim-lspconfig (lazy.nvim example)

~~~lua
{
  "neovim/nvim-lspconfig",
  version = false,
  dependencies = {
    "WillEhrendreich/Ionide-Nvim",
  },
  opts = {
    servers = {
      fsautocomplete = require("ionide").setup({}),
    },
  },
}
~~~

## Usage

Opening `*.fs`, `*.fsi`, `*.fsx`, or `*.fsproj` files triggers Ionide-Nvim.

### Commands

#### LSP Commands
- `:IonideRestartLspClient` — Restart the LSP client
- `:IonideReloadProjects` — Reload workspace projects
- `:IonideDocumentation` — Show formatted F# documentation using FsAutoComplete's richer docs endpoint

#### F# Interactive
- `:IonideSendCurrentLineToFSI` — Send current line to FSI
- `:IonideSendSelectionToFSI` — Send visual selection to FSI
- `:IonideSendWholeBufferToFSI` — Send entire buffer to FSI
- `:IonideToggleFSI` — Toggle FSI window
- `:IonideQuitFSI` — Quit FSI
- `:IonideResetFSI` — Reset FSI session

> **Tip:** For cell-based evaluation, inline results, and live testing, see [sagefs.nvim](https://github.com/WillEhrendreich/sagefs.nvim).

#### fsproj File Operations
- `:IonideFsprojAddFile <fsproj> <file>` — Add new file to project
- `:IonideFsprojAddExistingFile <fsproj> <file>` — Add existing file to project
- `:IonideFsprojAddFileAbove <fsproj> <currentFile> <newFile>` — Add a file above another file
- `:IonideFsprojAddFileBelow <fsproj> <currentFile> <newFile>` — Add a file below another file
- `:IonideFsprojMoveFileUp <fsproj> <file>` — Move file up in compile order
- `:IonideFsprojMoveFileDown <fsproj> <file>` — Move file down in compile order
- `:IonideFsprojRemoveFile <fsproj> <file>` — Remove file from project
- `:IonideFsprojRenameFile <fsproj> <oldFile> <newName>` — Rename file in project

#### Tests
- `:IonideTestDiscover` — Ask FsAutoComplete to discover tests
- `:IonideTestRun [filter]` — Ask FsAutoComplete to run tests, optionally filtered

#### Documentation
- `:IonideDocumentation` — Show formatted F# documentation using FsAutoComplete's richer docs pipeline

### Settings

## Responsibility split: Neovim vs LazyVim vs Ionide

Ionide-Nvim is intentionally a **thin wrapper around FsAutoComplete** rather than a replacement for Neovim's built-in LSP UX.

In a modern setup, responsibilities are usually split like this:

### Neovim built-in LSP already handles
- standard LSP request/response plumbing
- hover windows and floating preview support
- semantic tokens engine
- built-in APIs like `vim.lsp.buf.hover()`, `vim.lsp.buf.rename()`, `vim.lsp.codelens.refresh()`, etc.

### LazyVim often already handles
- generic LSP keymaps
- inlay hints enablement
- folds via `vim.lsp.foldexpr()`
- general editor-wide LSP ergonomics

### Ionide-Nvim should mainly handle
- FsAutoComplete custom methods like `fsharp/documentation`, `fsharp/workspacePeek`, `test/runTests`, `fsproj/*`, etc.
- FsAutoComplete custom notifications
- F#-specific workspace/project behavior
- optional F#-specific extras that are not already owned by your global Neovim/LazyVim setup

In other words: if Neovim or LazyVim already does something generically and well, Ionide should usually **not duplicate it**.

